Fix gpsp core compilation platform setting for arm64 target architecture.

The GBA core (gpsp) makefile in MinUI overrides gpsp_MAKE to make platform=unix.
This causes it to target x86 dynarec assembly when compiled on a x86_64 container host.
By setting platform=arm64, we force it to target arm64, which compiles cleanly on
our aarch64 cross-compiler.

Upstream: N/A
Signed-off-by: Antigravity <antigravity@google.com>

diff --git a/workspace/minime/cores/makefile b/workspace/minime/cores/makefile
index 71afc84..9d42fa6 100644
--- a/workspace/minime/cores/makefile
+++ b/workspace/minime/cores/makefile
@@ -32,7 +32,7 @@ snes9x2005_plus_REPO = https://github.com/libretro/snes9x2005
 # Override make commands to compile with platform=unix for 64-bit Linux compatibility
 fceumm_MAKE = make platform=unix
 gambatte_MAKE = make platform=unix
-gpsp_MAKE = make platform=unix
+gpsp_MAKE = make platform=arm64
 pcsx_rearmed_MAKE = make -f Makefile.libretro platform=unix
 picodrive_MAKE = make -f Makefile.libretro platform=unix GIT_REVISION=""
 snes9x2005_plus_MAKE = make platform=unix USE_BLARGG_APU=1
